    fix(forge-tui): Fix Option<Debouncer> type handling and add test serialization

    - Changed _debouncer field from Debouncer to Option<Debouncer> to allow
      proper cleanup via take() in stop() method
    - Added stop() method to StatusWatcher that properly consumes and stops
      the debouncer
    - Added Drop implementation that calls stop() for automatic cleanup
    - Fixed start_watching() to handle Option<Debouncer> correctly
    - Added #[serial(file_watcher)] attribute to tests that create StatusWatcher
      instances to serialize file watcher tests
    - Added global TEST_WATCHER_MUTEX for test serialization

    Note: Some tests still fail due to inotify file descriptor exhaustion when
    run together. This requires a more significant fix (e.g., using PollWatcher
    in tests or mocking file watching). The code changes are correct and tests
    pass when run individually or by module.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

